ranking purposes. FMFs were then applied in order to determine the criteria weights to be used in the development of a landslide susceptibility map. Finally, a 
landslide inventory database was used to validate the LSM map by comparing it with known landslides within the study area. Results indicated that the 
integration of fuzzy set theory with AHP produced significantly improved accuracies and a high level of reliability in the resulting landslide susceptibility 
map. Approximately 53\% of known landslides within our study area fell within zones classified as having “very high susceptibility”, with the further 31\% 
falling into zones classified as having “high susceptibility”., 
          
            
